cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC

This paper involves the use of machine learning (ML) techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), to improve branch prediction accuracy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AR (Computer Architecture and Embedded Systems), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) to some extent, but these categories are less relevant to the main focus of the paper.
